================================================================================
SERVICENOW DATA IMPORT — CSA 2025 NOTES
================================================================================

1) WHY DATA IMPORT IS NEEDED
----------------------------
• Used to bulk load data into ServiceNow.
• Avoids manual record creation.
• Common use cases:
   - Users & Groups (from Active Directory)
   - HR employee data
   - Knowledge articles
   - Assets and CMDB data

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) WAYS TO IMPORT DATA INTO SERVICENOW
--------------------------------------

A) IMPORT XML
• Imports XML files only.
• Mostly used to move data between ServiceNow instances.
• Table is auto-detected from XML content.

B) IMPORT (LIST CONTEXT MENU)
• Used to import Excel files.
• Uses Import Sets and Transform Maps internally.

C) IMPORT SETS (CORE MECHANISM)
• Primary and recommended way to import data.
• Supports multiple data sources.
• Uses staging tables and transform logic.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3) ROLES REQUIRED
-----------------
• admin
• import_admin

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4) IMPORT SET ARCHITECTURE (VERY IMPORTANT)
-------------------------------------------
Import process flow:

Data Source
   ↓
Import Set Table (Staging Table)
   ↓
Transform Map
   ↓
Target Table

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5) IMPORT SET COMPONENTS
------------------------

A) DATA SOURCE
• Defines where data comes from.
• Examples:
   - File (Excel / CSV)
   - Attachment
   - LDAP
   - JDBC

--------------------------------------

B) IMPORT SET TABLE
• Temporary staging table.
• Stores raw imported data.
• Table name is auto-generated.
• Data is NOT directly inserted into target table.

--------------------------------------

C) TRANSFORM MAP
• Maps source fields to target table fields.
• Controls how data is inserted or updated.
• Can be:
   - Auto-mapped
   - Manually mapped

--------------------------------------

D) TARGET TABLE
• Final table where data is stored.
• Example:
   - incident
   - sys_user
   - custom tables

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6) COALESCE FIELDS (EXAM-CRITICAL)
---------------------------------
• Coalesce field determines **Insert vs Update** behavior.
• If a matching record exists:
   → Record is UPDATED.
• If no match exists:
   → New record is INSERTED.

Common coalesce fields:
• sys_id
• number
• email

NOTE:
• Without coalesce → records are always inserted.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7) DATA POLICY (IMPORTANT)
--------------------------
• Enforces data rules at database level.
• Applies to:
   - UI
   - Import Sets
   - Web Services

Common use cases:
• Make fields mandatory.
• Prevent invalid or incomplete data import.

IMPORTANT:
• "Apply to Import Sets" must be enabled.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8) DIFFERENCE: UI POLICY vs DATA POLICY
---------------------------------------
• UI Policy:
   - Applies only to UI.
   - Does NOT affect imports.

• Data Policy:
   - Applies to UI + Import Sets + APIs.
   - Blocks invalid data insertion.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9) IMPORT RESULT TRACKING
-------------------------
• Each import creates a log record.
• Shows:
   - Inserted records
   - Updated records
   - Skipped records
   - Errors

Used for:
• Monitoring
• Troubleshooting failed imports

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
10) KEY CSA EXAM TAKEAWAYS
--------------------------
• Import Sets are the core import mechanism.
• Data flows via staging table before target table.
• Transform Maps control field mapping.
• Coalesce fields decide insert vs update.
• Data Policies enforce mandatory rules during import.
• UI Policies do NOT affect imports.

================================================================================
END OF DATA IMPORT — CSA 2025
================================================================================
